      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack will cool hardly at all during the overcast night. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack below approximately 3000 m. The high humditiy will give rise in the afternoon to a loss of strength within the snowpack also on steep shady slopes. <br/> Steep west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2500 m: Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
      },
